          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Janice Pereira"
          },
          "datePublished": "2024-09-29",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "It's quite late to write a review but still writing. I had visited here on 7th July 24 for CTET exam being a centre. The school management only aimed at earning money from the candidates. According to our admit card we were told to report at 12 noon for 2.00 pm paper. But the school management didn't bother about this at all. So many candidates were made to stand outside the main gate in rain on road. Many of them had travelled from far off places but still they didn't care neither allowed us to see the classroom allotment. After requesting several times they finally opened the main gate at around 1.00 pm. Later we were told to pay Rs. 40 to keep our bags in locker which was not mentioned anywhere and every other centre allowed students to keep bags outside the class in the corridor. But this school had their own rules and tried taking advantage of helpless candidates who could have no option but to pay the amount. We were told that if your valuables are misplaced then the school isn't responsible and we have to leave our bag outside the school on the bench. It was totally disgusting to hear. The school management is horrible. Imagine collecting Rs. 40 per student from thousands of students. \"Shatiniketan good strategy to earn money.\" 👏🏻👏🏻👏🏻",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "Shantiniketan Public School - Panvel"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Komal Malviya"
          },
          "datePublished": "2024-07-08",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Attended the CTET exam at Shantiniketan Public School, New Panvel, on 07/07/24, and was shocked to discover a ₹40 bag storage fee without any secure facilities. Despite over 200+ candidates present—all future teachers—no one spoke up. When I raised my voice, the principal dismissively responded, and the police officer misbehaved with me, undermining my concerns. This practice seems both illegal and unethical. My question is, is this ethically right? What message is this school promoting? Shame on the school. If our bags aren't safe with a police officer present, how can we trust student safety? @NTA_Exams, please investigate and ensure fair treatment for all students. #CTET #ExamIssues #StudentRights #UnethicalPractices #EducationalEthics #SchoolSafety #SpeakUp #FutureTeachers",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
